cs.ET, cs.NE, cs.EM, cs.EL, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the development of a circuit for copying the value of a resistor into a memristive device, which falls under the category of electronic circuits and systems (cs.ET). The potential applications of memristors in artificial brains and neuro-science suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and embedded systems (cs.EM). The use of HSPICE simulations indicates that the paper could also be classified under the sub-categories of electronics (cs.EL) and systems and control (cs.SY).
